DURBAN - The Convener for National Executive Committee Deployees in KwaZulu-Natal Nocawe Mafu has called on party members in KZN to work on rebuilding the party ahead of the upcoming conferences. Mafu was speaking at the party's KZN 110 years anniversary at the Mpophomeni Sports Grounds, in Howick. She said KwaZulu-Natal is the party's strong hold and that members need to work around the clock in its rebuilding. She said all members from branch to provincial level - must focus their energy the party's renewal. "Take your space, take your role very seriously  and make sure that you do nothing but build the ANC". [HAPPENING NOW] The ANC in KwaZulu-Natal is celebrating the partys 110 years anniversary, the event follows the main celebration which was held in Polokwane, Limpopo last week.KZN provincial chairperson Sihle Zikalala will address todays gathering in the province. #ANCKZN110 pic.twitter.com/ooK5MdbsmP 